                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115 European War 1939/7563: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-29">October 29,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received October 30—2:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6759. American interests Japan. Department’s 2479, October 9. Foreign Office note
                    October 27 states Swiss Legation, Tokyo, reports internees in all camps visited
                    by its delegates in Japan and Korea do not work. Notwithstanding it has
                    submitted Japanese Government question raised Department’s 2479.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
